43 that has been obtained in violation of subsections (b), (c), or (d) of this Code section shall
44 be guilty of gift card theft.
45 (f) Any person who is convicted of violating subsection (b), (c), (d), or (e) of this Code
46 section shall be punished;
47 (1) As for a misdemeanor, if the value of all money, goods, services, and other things of
48 value obtained in violation of this Code section is less than $500.00;
49 (2) By imprisonment for not less than one nor more than ten years and a fine not to
50 exceed $5,000.00, if the amount of all money, goods, services, and other things of value
51 obtained in violation of this Code section is $500.00 or more; or
52 (3) By imprisonment for not less than one nor more than ten years and a fine nor to
53 exceed $5,000.00, if the amount of all money, goods, services, and other things of value
54 obtained in violation of this Code section exceeds $500.00 in any consecutive six-month
55 period."
56 SECTION 2.
57 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
